Title:
Hecate — Custom WhisperGate-themed Web UI for Mythic C2 (v3)

Type:
GitHub Tool

Short Summary (4–8 sentences max):
- Hecate is an alternative operator web interface for Mythic C2 v3 that replaces Mythic’s default React UI without requiring any Mythic server modifications.  
- It connects directly to Mythic’s existing GraphQL and WebSocket subscription APIs and is deployed as a Dockerized HTTPS-only nginx-served frontend.  
- The UI focuses on operator workflow improvements: live callback management, multi-select tasking with tab completion, snippet library, interactive output rendering (file/process browsers), and fleet-wide beacon health.  
- It adds visualization and reporting features such as pivot graphs (SOCKS/P2P edges), timeline views, session replay, and MITRE ATT&CK coverage overlays with Navigator JSON export.  
- Useful primarily for red teams and penetration testers running Mythic who want better operational visibility, tasking ergonomics, and reporting artifacts.  
- Interesting because it demonstrates a full-featured third-party Mythic UI built purely on the public API surface (GraphQL/subscriptions) and packaged for reproducible deployment.

Technical Focus:
- Mythic C2 GraphQL queries/mutations and WebSocket subscriptions (`graphql-ws`)
- React 19 + Vite 6 frontend architecture (TypeScript)
- Apollo Client integration and real-time state handling (Zustand)
- Operator workflow UX: tasking, output parsing, callback health telemetry
- Pivoting/topology visualization (SOCKS, P2P links) and session replay
- Docker + nginx HTTPS reverse proxying to `mythic_nginx:7443`

Use Cases:
- Deploy a custom operator UI for Mythic C2 operations (lab or team server)
- Improve multi-callback tasking efficiency (snippets, command palette, batching)
- Visualize pivots/tunnels and track lateral movement paths during ops
- Generate ATT&CK-mapped activity summaries and export Navigator layers
- Review operations via timeline/session replay for debriefs and reporting

Keywords:
Mythic C2, GraphQL, WebSocket subscriptions, graphql-ws, Apollo Client, React 19, Vite 6, TypeScript, Zustand, Docker Compose, nginx, HTTPS, self-signed certificate, callback management, tasking UI, SOCKS pivoting, P2P routing, MITRE ATT&CK, ATT&CK Navigator JSON, session replay, timeline visualization